The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	 Bengal may have to do with only one preparatory tournament in the lead up to the Ranji Trophy as the dates of the Moin-ud Dowlah Gold Cup in Hyderabad are clashing with those of the JP Atray tournament in Chandigarh.      
	The Hyderabad meet will be held from September 10-25. The Cricket Association of Bengal joint secretary Biswarup Dey said on Thursday that they may have to skip the JP Atray. We cant help it. Though we had planned to participate in both the tournaments, we may ultimately have to choose one because of the circumstances. We may skip the Chandigarh tournament, he said.          
	 The Bengal Olympic Association (BOA) and the Indian Football Association (IFA) will hold condolence meetings in the memory of the late sports minister Subhas Chakraborty. The BOAs programme is scheduled to be held at the Rotary Sadan on August 12. The IFAs meeting will be held on August 17 at the Moulali Yuva Kendra.                
	 The West Bengal Athletics Association announced the names of the athletes in different age-group categories for the 21st East Zone Junior National Championships to be held from August 16-18 in Bhubaneswar. Sukhen Mondal was named boys coach while Arabinda Dey will be in charge of the girls.                                                                                                                                                                       
